          <div><h6>Vol. 1-3</h6>
            <span>Denji's a poor young man who'll do anything for money, even hunting down Devils with his pet devil-dog Pochita. He's a simple man with simple dreams, drowning under a mountain of debt. But his sad life gets turned upside down when he's betrayed by someone he trusts. Now with the power of a Devil inside him, Denji's become a whole new man-Chainsaw Man!</span>
          </div> 
        </div>
        <div class="column" aria-role="button">
          <div><h6>Vol. 4-6</h6>
            <span>Devil Extermination Special Division 4 is in serious trouble as a devil has sent a whole team of assassins to take Denji's heart. In order to survive the onslaught, Denji, Power and Aki will have to get stronger. But is Denji smart enough to learn how to control his devil powers? Can you can teach an old chainsaw-dog-devil new tricks?</span> 
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column" aria-role="button">
          <div><h6>Vol. 7-9</h6>
            <span>Denji and company are planning a trip to Enoshima when it is discovered that the news managed to secure a video of Denji as Chainsaw Man. The unwanted publicity leads to a whole new set of problems for the gang and paints a larger target on Denji’s back. Instead of facing off against other devils, Denji is now facing assassins from countries all over the world. </span> 
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column" aria-role="button">
          <div><h6>Vol. 10-12</h6>
            <span>Having been forced to kill a friend, Denji finds that his brain has turned to mush from despair. Without the motivation to keep going, he seeks help from Makima. But Makima is not what she appears, and Denji’s pain is only just beginning. Her affinity with Chainsaw Man is strong; to consume or be consumed. She is treating Denji like her puppet/dog.</span> 
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column" aria-role="button">
          <div><h6>Vol. 13-15</h6>
            <span>Denji is desperate to tell the world that he’s Chainsaw Man, but is he competent enough to pull off a proper reveal? Meanwhile, Asa has made a friend! But this new friendship may be hiding a dark secret. Denji can't help but want to find out that he's a Chainsaw Man. That desire ignores Yoshida, who continues to monitor him...!?</span> 
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column" aria-role="button">
          <div><h6>Vol. 16+</h6>
            <span>To live life as a normal high school student, or to become Chainsaw Man again? Denji is facing the ultimate choice and has no idea what to do. Meanwhile, a mysterious group called the Chainsaw Man Church is gaining power behind the scenes. What exactly are they plotting, and how will Denji fit into their scheme?</span> 
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column" aria-role="button">
          <div><h6 style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-left: -0.125rem;">More Wrks</h6>
            <span>Before Chainsaw Man is a series of books compiling the self-contained stories that Fujimoto wrote before the serialization of Chainsaw Man, and they paint a picture of how he has refined his writing style throughout the years. If you’re keen to read more from this unique author and want to follow his journey to see how he developed his writing and draw from his start in the industry to Chainsaw Man, these volumes will be interesting. </span> 
          </div>
